Fauxan <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fauxknight>Fauxknight</A> at: 5/15/03 3:54:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/03 4:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=571.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Great Norrath Rally</span><hr size=1> Um, the way I read it is the entry fee covers the prize money. 500p per person (or team) times 10 teams equals 5,000p, which, is what the prize is. <br>
<br>
As for setting up the rules to guarntee no loss, well, yeah, but also no loss to anyone else, if there aren't ten teams, no contest, people get thier money back. If no one team completes the Rally, they get their money back.<br>
<br>
As for an event not being about making money. That seems a little to highbrow. This guy is taking the time to set this up, he's gonna spend at least 5 or 6 hours of his time doing this. Granted, we don't know what he has planned it could suck and be a total washout. <br>
<br>
It's very common for these types of rallys to have the entry fee cover the prize money, in real life. This is alot better then a casino, which are just annoying and fill the air with spam. You have a better chance of winning this then with the casinos, since over time, your going to lose if you keep playing at a casino. That;s why casinos are rich rich rich. The laws of average say that you will lose in time.<br>
<br>
It kinda feels like some people are far to synical about something when they see a number like 500p. Give the guy a break. He's trying something that sounds more interesting then people setting up casinos with the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>ONLY</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> intention of making money sitting around. There is even a cleric that will give you free temprance if you bet and lose. But I be the minimum bet is at leas the cost or more of a peridot. <br>
<br>
Maybe you should all talk to Geax in game before tearing this down. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=louduc>louduc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/03 5:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=571.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Great Norrath Rally</span><hr size=1> It is not surprising that some people find it expansive. When I decided to charge such a fee, I saw it more like a team fee. I believe it is a good opportunity for guilds to compete with each other and kill the fee by dividing it among 5, 10 or more teammates. <br>
<br>
The point of this event is for people to have fun doing it as much as I did preparing it. I really don't care about the money really. I asked some friends of mine to help me during to events and I promised I would pay them for their time. Plus, I can't afford to pay 5000pp to the winning team from my own money. I also thought of returning a certain % of the entry fee as a grand prize but participants wouldn't be interested in what they MIGHT get if they win. <br>
<br>
If money is the only thing that bothers potentiel participants, i am open to suggestions. <br>
<br>
